name: .3DMARK-RESULT File Extension
summary: Learn about .3DMARK-RESULT files and view a list of programs that open them.

description: Results file used by 3DMark, an application used to benchmark the 3D gaming capability of a Windows computer; contains a computer's DirectX performance results initiated by the 3DMark test.

content: You can upload your result file to the 3DMark website to save them in one place and compare them with other users.
NOTE: 3DMark results files may also use the .3DR file extension.
